<CAPTION>  Drawings (4); DRAWING:: New York Times; Most partition walls are made of
2-by-4 lumber strips fastened together in rectangular framework.; DRAWING:
Framework's top piece, the plate, is attached to the ceiling. Location for
sill is marked directly underneath.; DRAWING:Fasten sill to floor with nails
